: : Kup : :
Kup(via commlink): Aye, lad. If the shields keep it away then it will evntually blow by. But we could still use a vaccine for later use.
 CatMaster o <catmastero@...> wrote:Kenzo ran to a window to see the oncoming plauge "Are the force
shields up?" He said back over the com link to Kup.

--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, Richard Allen <roborick007@y...> wrote:
> 
> : : Kup : : 
> Kup looks out and sees the rusty haze for himself. 
> Kup: Oh slag! Of all the damn things to happen... 
> Kup slams his fist into a near by computer terminal, putting the
ship on red alert. The alarms sound as the ship seals off, and the
deflector shields activate. 
> He then opens a comm to every Maximal in the base. 
> Kup: This is security chief Kup. We have reason to believe that a
very infections and lethal plague is airborn and heading this way. If
you are infected you will not notice symptoms at first, but will later
encounter small glitches, and eventually decay of rust. Do not leave
the base untill informed otherwise. 
> Kup runs for the Commanders office. 
> Kup: Come with me Aerotaur. I guess the attack on the Predacons that
Katya and I were planning will be delayed even more. 
> He reaches the office and finds only Yggdrasil inside. 
> Kup: Commander, I'm sure you heard my report over the comm. I'm not
sure what to do. And where is Rodimus Prime?
